2500|$|On July 17, President Bill Clinton {{spoke with}} Kennedy's sister, Caroline, and later called his uncle, Ted. Clinton also spoke with Andrew Cuomo, {{who at the}} time was married to Kennedy's cousin, Kerry. [...] "He wanted to let them know he was {{thinking}} about them, that we'll do everything we can, and that our prayers are with them", Clinton spokesman <b>Joe</b> <b>Lockhart</b> said. Clinton ordered warships of the U.S. Navy to assist in the search for Kennedy's plane. Critics argued that the search was an abuse of taxpayer dollars, as no ordinary citizen would receive similar treatment. Clinton said that afternoon that the Kennedys had [...] "suffered much, and given more", and also called for them to feel [...] "the strength of God, the love of their friends and the prayers of their fellow citizens".|$|E
