50|$|Huckabay, being a small {{community}}, did {{not have}} many churches. The Church of Christ was an early church that was built in 1876. The community also had two other churches, the Baptist Church and the Methodist Church, both which were organized in 1881. John Haven organized the Methodist while <b>Joe</b> <b>Lockhart</b> the Baptist.|$|E
